    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your note No. 122, of 16th instant, I
                    have the honor to inform you that I am duly authorized by Her Majesty’s
                    Government to assent, and do hereby assent, to the agreement therein proposed,
                    empowering the scientists of both nationalities now proceeding to the Pribilof
                    Islands to kill fur seals to such extent and in such manner as the purposes of
                    their investigations may require.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
